The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 December is 9,317 (1,078.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 November, there were 529 new confirmed cases (61.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 November, there were 828 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 36% (299 fewer cases).
